Because a single gathering of 24 folded sheets would not lie flat, stationers would often break the 24-sheet quires into smaller units, for instance, into two separate groupings of 12 sheets apiece, or 24 leaves each.<lb/>
Thus, a complete 24-sheet quire could contain two sub-quires.<lb/>
