the chapter was revised and recopied only at a later stage, as Brontë did not<lb/>
entirely decide on the title <hi>Shirley</hi> until August 24, 1849—long after she had<lb/>
first sent the manuscript volume 1 to her publisher in February; before that, the<lb/>
novel had been tentatively referred to as <hi>Hollow’s Mill</hi>, a title that was ultimately<lb/>
