  Brontë seems to have anticipated this very criticism. At the outset of this late expansion, her narrator addresses the novel’s readers as follows: “Yet again, a passage from the <hi>blank book</hi>, if you like, reader; if you don’t like it, pass it over:—.”<sup>151</sup><lb/>
